50|$|Sir George Frederick Lawrence Charles (7 June 1916 - 26 June 2004) is {{a former}} trade unionist, politician, founder of the Saint <b>Lucia</b> <b>Labour</b> <b>Party</b> and Chief Minister of Saint Lucia (1 January 1960 - April 1964). He is a {{recipient}} of Saint Lucia's second-highest honour, the <b>St.</b> <b>Lucia</b> Cross (1987), and was knighted in 1988 by Queen Elizabeth II. George F. L. Charles Airport, in Castries, Saint Lucia, is named in his honour.|$|R
50|$|The {{last two}} {{elections}} in 1997 and 2001 had seen victories for the Saint <b>Lucia</b> <b>Labour</b> <b>Party</b> {{with the previous}} election in 2001 seeing them win 14 seats to only 3 for the United Workers Party.|$|R
